rComments: One of the best instructors I've ever had! He made learning lambda calculus interesting and fun, despite the difficulty of the subject. His lectures were clear and he provided amazing handouts that clearly took time and effort to prepare. A dedicated and enthusiastic instructor.

Enthusiastic and engaging lecturer. Sometimes gets a little distracted but has very clear printed lecture notes that make up for it. The abstract material is challenging for some but he does not bog it down with rhetoric. Would highly recommend to others with an interest in semantics.
